Refresh Token Flow (VERY IMPORTANT)
🧩 Problem - JWT expires quickly (security)
👉 What happens after expiry?
    ✅ Solution: Refresh Token
      You issue 2 tokens:
      Token	            Purpose      	Expiry
      Access Token	    API access	  Short (15 min)
      Refresh Token	    Get new token	Long (7 days)

1. Login: → Access Token + Refresh Token
2. API calls: → Use Access Token
3. If expired:→ Send Refresh Token
4. Server:→ Validate Refresh Token  → Issue new Access Token

    @PostMapping("/refresh")
    public String refresh(@RequestBody String refreshToken) {
        if (isValid(refreshToken)) {
            return generateNewAccessToken();
        }
        throw new RuntimeException("Invalid refresh token");
    }

Best Practices:
      Store refresh token in DB
      Use HttpOnly cookies
      Rotate refresh tokens (important 🔥)
⚠️ Common Mistakes:
      ❌ Storing refresh token in localStorage
      ❌ Not expiring refresh tokens
      ❌ No rotation → security risk


