JWT — best for stateless REST APIs and microservices, you manage tokens yourself
OAuth2 — best for social login (Google, GitHub) or delegated access to third-party APIs
SAML — best for enterprise SSO with corporate identity providers (Okta, ADFS, Azure AD)
Always use BCryptPasswordEncoder — never store plain passwords
Use @PreAuthorize with SpEL for fine-grained method-level access control
SessionCreationPolicy.STATELESS is essential for JWT — disables server-side sessions

